{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":800,"text":"I come from one of the most liberal,"},{"time":4320,"text":"tolerant, progressive places\nin the United States,"},{"time":7560,"text":"Seattle, Washington."},{"time":9480,"text":"And I grew up with a family\nof great Seattlites."},{"time":13400,"text":"My mother was an artist,\nmy father was a college professor,"},{"time":17240,"text":"and I am truly grateful for my upbringing,"},{"time":19800,"text":"because I always felt completely\ncomfortable designing my life"},{"time":24320,"text":"exactly as I saw fit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27000,"text":"And in point of fact,"},{"time":28360,"text":"I took a route that was not exactly\nwhat my parents had in mind."},{"time":31480,"text":"When I was 19, I dropped out of college --"},{"time":35120,"text":"dropped out, kicked out, splitting hairs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37200,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":40680,"text":"And I went on the road\nas a professional French horn player,"},{"time":44960,"text":"which was my lifelong dream."},{"time":46680,"text":"I played chamber music\nall over the United States and Europe,"},{"time":49600,"text":"and I toured for a couple of years"},{"time":51400,"text":"with a great jazz guitar player\nnamed Charlie Bird."},{"time":54400,"text":"And by the end of my 20s,"},{"time":56000,"text":"I wound up as a member of the Barcelona\nSymphony Orchestra in Spain."},{"time":60200,"text":"What a great life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61440,"text":"And you know, my parents never complained."},{"time":65040,"text":"They supported me all the way through it."},{"time":67040,"text":"It wasn't their dream."},{"time":68960,"text":"They used to tell\ntheir neighbors and friends,"},{"time":71127,"text":"\"Our son, he's taking a gap decade.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":74200,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":76880,"text":"And --"},{"time":78800,"text":"There was, however, one awkward\nconversation about my lifestyle"},{"time":83720,"text":"that I want to tell you about."},{"time":85200,"text":"I was 27, and I was home from Barcelona,"},{"time":88000,"text":"and I was visiting\nmy parents for Christmas,"},{"time":90720,"text":"and I was cooking dinner with my mother,\nand we were alone in the kitchen."},{"time":95240,"text":"And she was quiet, too quiet."},{"time":98080,"text":"Something was wrong."},{"time":99560,"text":"And so I said, \"Mom, what's on your mind?\""},{"time":102760,"text":"And she said, \"Your dad and I\nare really worried about you.\""},{"time":107040,"text":"And I said, \"What?\"\nI mean, what could it be, at this point?"},{"time":109960,"text":"And she said, \"I want you to be\ncompletely honest with me:"},{"time":113680,"text":"have you been voting for Republicans?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":115640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":120680,"text":"Now, the truth is,"},{"time":122080,"text":"I wasn't really political,\nI was just a French horn player."},{"time":126480,"text":"But I had a bit of an epiphany,"},{"time":130039,"text":"and they had detected it,\nand it was causing some confusion."},{"time":132920,"text":"You see, I had become\nan enthusiast for capitalism,"},{"time":138200,"text":"and I want to tell you why that is."},{"time":140840,"text":"It stems from a lifelong interest of mine"},{"time":145000,"text":"in, believe it or not, poverty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147920,"text":"See, when I was a kid\ngrowing up in Seattle,"},{"time":150280,"text":"I remember the first time\nI saw real poverty."},{"time":153920,"text":"We were a lower middle class family,\nbut that's of course not real poverty."},{"time":158320,"text":"That's not even close."},{"time":160080,"text":"The first time I saw poverty,\nand poverty's face,"},{"time":163520,"text":"was when I was six\nor seven years old, early 1970s."},{"time":166360,"text":"And it was like a lot of you,\nkind of a prosaic example, kind of trite."},{"time":170920,"text":"It was a picture in the National\nGeographic Magazine"},{"time":174320,"text":"of a kid who was my age in East Africa,"},{"time":178640,"text":"and there were flies on his face\nand a distended belly."},{"time":181240,"text":"And he wasn't going to make it,\nand I knew that, and I was helpless."},{"time":186720,"text":"Some of you remember that picture,"},{"time":188720,"text":"not exactly that picture,\none just like it."},{"time":190760,"text":"It introduced the West\nto grinding poverty around the world."},{"time":196240,"text":"Well, that vision kind of haunted me\nas I grew up and I went to school"},{"time":201040,"text":"and I dropped out and dropped in"},{"time":202840,"text":"and started my family."},{"time":205496,"text":"And I wondered, what happened to that kid?"},{"time":207520,"text":"Or to people just like him\nall over the world?"},{"time":211200,"text":"And so I started to study,\neven though I wasn't in college,"},{"time":214000,"text":"I was looking for the answer:"},{"time":215440,"text":"what happened to the world's\npoorest people?"},{"time":217560,"text":"Has it gotten worse?\nHas it gotten better? What?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":219840,"text":"And I found the answer,\nand it changed my life,"},{"time":222640,"text":"and I want to share it with you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":225040,"text":"See --"},{"time":227760,"text":"most Americans believe\nthat poverty has gotten worse"},{"time":232040,"text":"since we were children,\nsince they saw that vision."},{"time":235200,"text":"If you ask Americans, \"Has poverty\ngotten worse or better around the world?\","},{"time":238880,"text":"70 percent will say that hunger\nhas gotten worse since the early 1970s."},{"time":242240,"text":"But here's the truth."},{"time":243760,"text":"Here's the epiphany that I had\nthat changed my thinking."},{"time":247480,"text":"From 1970 until today,"},{"time":250880,"text":"the percentage of the world's population"},{"time":253760,"text":"living in starvation levels,"},{"time":255800,"text":"living on a dollar a day or less,\nobviously adjusted for inflation,"},{"time":259480,"text":"that percentage has declined"},{"time":262720,"text":"by 80 percent."},{"time":265080,"text":"There's been an 80 percent decline\nin the world's worst poverty"},{"time":268080,"text":"since I was a kid."},{"time":269320,"text":"And I didn't even know about it."},{"time":270920,"text":"This, my friends, that's a miracle."},{"time":273320,"text":"That's something we ought to celebrate."},{"time":275640,"text":"It's the greatest antipoverty achievement\nin the history of mankind,"},{"time":279920,"text":"and it happened in our lifetimes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282480,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":286040,"text":"So when I learned this, I asked,\nwhat did that? What made it possible?"},{"time":290920,"text":"Because if you don't know why,\nyou can't do it again."},{"time":293760,"text":"If you want to replicate it"},{"time":295120,"text":"and get the next two billion\npeople out of poverty,"},{"time":297680,"text":"because that's what we're talking about:\nsince I was a kid,"},{"time":300480,"text":"two billion of the least of these,\nour brothers and sisters,"},{"time":303316,"text":"have been pulled out of poverty."},{"time":304880,"text":"I want the next two billion,\nso I've got to know why."},{"time":307386,"text":"And I went in search of an answer."},{"time":309040,"text":"And it wasn't a political answer,\nbecause I didn't care."},{"time":311720,"text":"You know what, I still don't care."},{"time":313400,"text":"I wanted the best answer\nfrom mainstream economists"},{"time":318240,"text":"left, right and center."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320880,"text":"And here it is."},{"time":322560,"text":"Here are the reasons."},{"time":323840,"text":"There are five reasons that two billion\nof our brothers and sisters"},{"time":327600,"text":"have been pulled out of poverty\nsince I was a kid."},{"time":330000,"text":"Number one: globalization."},{"time":333080,"text":"Number two: free trade."},{"time":335200,"text":"Number three: property rights."},{"time":337560,"text":"Number four: rule of law."},{"time":340120,"text":"Number five: entrepreneurship."},{"time":343120,"text":"It was the free enterprise system\nspreading around the world"},{"time":347400,"text":"after 1970 that did that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349200,"text":"Now, I'm not naive."},{"time":351640,"text":"I know that free enterprise isn't perfect,"},{"time":354120,"text":"and I know that free enterprise\nisn't everything we need"},{"time":357280,"text":"to build a better world."},{"time":358520,"text":"But that is great."},{"time":361080,"text":"And that's beyond politics."},{"time":362440,"text":"Here's what I learned.\nThis is the epiphany."},{"time":364560,"text":"Capitalism is not just about accumulation."},{"time":367600,"text":"At its best, it's about aspiration,"},{"time":370160,"text":"which is what so many people\non this stage talk about,"},{"time":372880,"text":"is the aspiration that comes from dreams"},{"time":376120,"text":"that are embedded\nin the free enterprise system."},{"time":378400,"text":"And we've got to share it\nwith more people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380600,"text":"Now, I want to tell you\nabout a second epiphany"},{"time":383840,"text":"that's related to that first one"},{"time":386360,"text":"that I think can bring us progress,\nnot just around the world,"},{"time":389440,"text":"but right here at home."},{"time":391840,"text":"The best quote I've ever heard"},{"time":393880,"text":"to summarize the thoughts\nthat I've just given you"},{"time":397480,"text":"about pulling people out of poverty"},{"time":399560,"text":"is as follows:"},{"time":401680,"text":"\"Free markets have created more wealth\nthan any system in history."},{"time":406560,"text":"They have lifted billions out of poverty.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":410400,"text":"Who said it?"},{"time":411680,"text":"It sounds like Milton Friedman\nor Ronald Reagan."},{"time":415800,"text":"Wrong."},{"time":417480,"text":"President Barack Obama said that."},{"time":420440,"text":"Why do I know it by heart?"},{"time":422960,"text":"Because he said it to me."},{"time":425640,"text":"Crazy."},{"time":427160,"text":"And I said, \"Hallelujah.\""},{"time":430800,"text":"But more than that, I said,"},{"time":433320,"text":"\"What an opportunity.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":435040,"text":"You know what I was thinking?"},{"time":436560,"text":"It was at an event\nthat we were doing on the subject"},{"time":439040,"text":"at Georgetown University in May of 2015."},{"time":441000,"text":"And I thought, this is the solution"},{"time":443800,"text":"to the biggest problem\nfacing America today. What?"},{"time":447320,"text":"It's coming together around these ideas,"},{"time":450120,"text":"liberals and conservatives,"},{"time":451880,"text":"to help people who need us the most."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455480,"text":"Now, I don't have to tell anybody\nin this room that we're in a crisis,"},{"time":458800,"text":"in America and many countries around\nthe world with political polarization."},{"time":462400,"text":"It's risen to critical, crisis levels."},{"time":464320,"text":"It's unpleasant. It's not right."},{"time":467320,"text":"There was an article last year"},{"time":469000,"text":"in the Proceedings\nof the National Academy of Sciences,"},{"time":471640,"text":"which is one of the most\nprestigious scientific journals"},{"time":476080,"text":"published in the West."},{"time":477360,"text":"And it was an article in 2014"},{"time":479840,"text":"on political motive asymmetry."},{"time":482280,"text":"What's that? That's what psychologists\ncall the phenomenon"},{"time":485019,"text":"of assuming that your ideology\nis based in love"},{"time":489440,"text":"but your opponents' ideology\nis based in hate."},{"time":492920,"text":"It's common in world conflict."},{"time":495760,"text":"You expect to see this between\nPalestinians and Israelis, for example."},{"time":500400,"text":"What the authors of this article found"},{"time":502840,"text":"was that in America today,\na majority of Republicans and Democrats"},{"time":507480,"text":"suffer from political motive asymmetry."},{"time":510080,"text":"A majority of people in our country today\nwho are politically active believe"},{"time":513960,"text":"that they are motivated by love\nbut the other side is motivated by hate."},{"time":517400,"text":"Think about it. Think about it."},{"time":518960,"text":"Most people are walking around saying,"},{"time":521159,"text":"\"You know, my ideology\nis based on basic benevolence,"},{"time":524360,"text":"I want to help people,"},{"time":525600,"text":"but the other guys,\nthey're evil and out to get me.\""},{"time":529200,"text":"You can't progress as a society\nwhen you have this kind of asymmetry."},{"time":534520,"text":"It's impossible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":536560,"text":"How do we solve it?"},{"time":537840,"text":"Well, first, let's be honest:\nthere are differences."},{"time":541520,"text":"Let's not minimize the differences.\nThat would be really naïve."},{"time":545240,"text":"There's a lot of good research on this."},{"time":547320,"text":"A veteran of the TED stage\nis my friend Jonathan Haidt."},{"time":550480,"text":"He's a psychology professor\nat New York University."},{"time":553560,"text":"He does work on the ideology\nand values and morals of different people"},{"time":558520,"text":"to see how they differ."},{"time":560360,"text":"And he's shown, for example,\nthat conservatives and liberals"},{"time":563194,"text":"have a very different emphasis\non what they think is important."},{"time":566234,"text":"For example, Jon Haidt has shown"},{"time":569560,"text":"that liberals care about poverty"},{"time":572560,"text":"59 percent more than they care\nabout economic liberty."},{"time":576280,"text":"And conservatives\ncare about economic liberty"},{"time":578800,"text":"28 percent more\nthan they care about poverty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582920,"text":"Irreconcilable differences, right?"},{"time":585000,"text":"We'll never come together. Wrong."},{"time":587520,"text":"That is diversity\nin which lies our strength."},{"time":590920,"text":"Remember what pulled up the poor."},{"time":595080,"text":"It was the obsession with poverty,"},{"time":598160,"text":"accompanied by the method\nof economic freedom"},{"time":602400,"text":"spreading around the world."},{"time":604040,"text":"We need each other, in other words,"},{"time":606600,"text":"if we want to help people and get the next\ntwo billion people out of poverty."},{"time":610244,"text":"There's no other way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612560,"text":"Hmm."},{"time":613920,"text":"How are we going to get that?"},{"time":616360,"text":"It's a tricky thing, isn't it."},{"time":618040,"text":"We need innovative thinking."},{"time":620280,"text":"A lot of it's on this stage."},{"time":621960,"text":"Social entrepreneurship.\nYeah. Absolutely. Phenomenal."},{"time":626280,"text":"We need investment overseas"},{"time":628640,"text":"in a sustainable, responsible,\nethical and moral way. Yes. Yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":633040,"text":"But you know what we really need?"},{"time":634880,"text":"We need a new day in flexible ideology."},{"time":639520,"text":"We need to be less predictable."},{"time":642680,"text":"Don't we?"},{"time":643920,"text":"Do you ever feel like your own ideology\nis starting to get predictable?"},{"time":648520,"text":"Kinda conventional?"},{"time":650280,"text":"Do you ever feel like you're always\nlistening to people who agree with you?"},{"time":654440,"text":"Why is that dangerous?"},{"time":656200,"text":"Because when we talk\nin this country about economics,"},{"time":659800,"text":"on the right, conservatives,"},{"time":661480,"text":"you're always talking about taxes\nand regulations and big government."},{"time":666880,"text":"And on the left, liberals,\nyou're talking about economics,"},{"time":669640,"text":"it's always about income inequality."},{"time":671920,"text":"Right? Now those are important things,"},{"time":675360,"text":"really important to me,\nreally important to you."},{"time":677640,"text":"But when it comes to lifting people up"},{"time":680200,"text":"who are starving and need us today,\nthose are distractions."},{"time":684680,"text":"We need to come together\naround the best ways"},{"time":688120,"text":"to mitigate poverty\nusing the best tools at our disposal,"},{"time":691480,"text":"and that comes only when conservatives\nrecognize that they need liberals"},{"time":696000,"text":"and their obsession with poverty,"},{"time":697640,"text":"and liberals need conservatives\nand their obsession with free markets."},{"time":703240,"text":"That's the diversity in which lies\nthe future strength of this country,"},{"time":707760,"text":"if we choose to take it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":710760,"text":"So how are we going to do it?\nHow are we going to do it together?"},{"time":713840,"text":"I've got to have some action items,\nnot just for you but for me."},{"time":717400,"text":"Number one. Action item number one:"},{"time":720320,"text":"remember, it's not good enough\njust to tolerate people who disagree."},{"time":725560,"text":"It's not good enough."},{"time":727280,"text":"We have to remember that we need\npeople who disagree with us,"},{"time":731200,"text":"because there are people\nwho need all of us"},{"time":733560,"text":"who are still waiting for these tools."},{"time":736680,"text":"Now, what are you going to do?\nHow are you going to express that?"},{"time":740000,"text":"Where does this start? It starts here."},{"time":741960,"text":"You know, all of us\nin this room, we're blessed."},{"time":745240,"text":"We're blessed with people\nwho listen to us."},{"time":747320,"text":"We're blessed with prosperity.\nWe're blessed with leadership."},{"time":750240,"text":"When people hear us,\nwith the kind of unpredictable ideology,"},{"time":755200,"text":"then maybe people will listen."},{"time":757640,"text":"Maybe progress will start at that point."},{"time":759840,"text":"That's number one. Number two."},{"time":762160,"text":"Number two: I'm asking you\nand I'm asking me"},{"time":766680,"text":"to be the person specifically\nwho blurs the lines,"},{"time":771080,"text":"who is ambiguous, who is hard to classify."},{"time":775160,"text":"If you're a conservative,"},{"time":776440,"text":"be the conservative\nwho is always going on about poverty"},{"time":780000,"text":"and the moral obligation\nto be a warrior for the poor."},{"time":782840,"text":"And if you're a liberal,\nbe a liberal who is always talking"},{"time":786560,"text":"about the beauty of free markets\nto solve our problems"},{"time":791160,"text":"when we use them responsibly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":793320,"text":"If we do that, we get two things."},{"time":796080,"text":"Number one: we get to start\nto work on the next two billion"},{"time":800680,"text":"and be the solution\nthat we've seen so much of in the past"},{"time":804240,"text":"and we need to see more of in the future.\nThat's what we get."},{"time":807160,"text":"And the second is\nthat we might just be able"},{"time":810160,"text":"to take the ghastly holy war of ideology\nthat we're suffering under in this country"},{"time":814840,"text":"and turn it into a competition of ideas"},{"time":819120,"text":"based on solidarity and mutual respect."},{"time":822120,"text":"And then maybe, just maybe,"},{"time":826000,"text":"we'll all realize that our big differences"},{"time":830360,"text":"aren't really that big after all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":833400,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":834640,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}